From: knsol <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH] fix: add disk-name = "SD" to sdmmc-disk DT node

WR_TRACE diagnostics with bigger CDC ringbuf showed main now reaches
mount_sd_card and disk_access_init returns -22 (-EINVAL). The SDHC
subsystem IS bound (no -ENODEV), but the disk pdrv name omi requests
("SD") doesn't match a registered disk.

Zephyr's binding for zephyr,sdmmc-disk requires disk-name. The omi
overlay's mmc {} child node didn't set it, so the disk registers
under whatever default the build environment picks (likely the
node's path or label, not "SD").

Set disk-name = "SD" explicitly so disk_access_init("SD") matches.
---
diff --git a/omi/firmware/devkit/overlay/xiao_ble_sense_devkitv1-spisd.overlay b/omi/firmware/devkit/overlay/xiao_ble_sense_devkitv1-spisd.overlay
--- a/omi/firmware/devkit/overlay/xiao_ble_sense_devkitv1-spisd.overlay
+++ b/omi/firmware/devkit/overlay/xiao_ble_sense_devkitv1-spisd.overlay
@@ -12,6 +12,7 @@
         mmc {
             compatible = "zephyr,sdmmc-disk";
             status = "okay";
+            disk-name = "SD";
         };
         spi-max-frequency = <1000000>;  // patch 0017: lowered 24 MHz → 1 MHz for SD init reliability
     };
